In fact, while we read a novel, we are insane  bonkers. We believe in the existence of people who arent there, we hear their voices, we watch the battle of Borodino with them, we may even become Napoleon. Sanity returns (in most cases) when the book is closed.
 Ursula K. Le Guin, The Left Hand of Darkness
