[Genre is] like working in any formin poetry, for example. When you work in form, be it a sonnet or villanelle or whatever, the form is there and you have to fill it. And you have to find how to make that form say what you want to say. But what you find, alwaysI think any poet whos worked in form will agree with meis that the form leads you to what you want to say. It is wonderful and mysterious.
 Ursula K. Le Guin
