People are supposed to be lean. You cant be too thin, everybody says so, especially anorexics. People are supposed to be lean and taut, because thats how men generally are, lean and taut, or anyhow thats how a lot of men start out and some of them even stay that way. And men are people, people are men, that has been well established, and so people, real people, the right kind of people, are lean. But Im really lousy at being people, because Im not lean at all but sort of podgy, with actual fat places. I am untaut.
 Ursula K. Le Guin, The Wave in the Mind: Talks and Essays on the Writer, the Reader, and the Imagination
