The lynx lives at the High Desert Museum. Briefly, when he was a kitten somebody pulled out his claws (declawing a cat is the same as pulling out a human beings fingernails and toenails or cutting off the last joint of each toe and finger). Then they pulled out his four great cat fangs. Then they pretended he was their itty-bitty kitty. Then they got tired of him, or got scared of him, and dumped him. He was found starving.
 Ursula K. Le Guin, No Time to Spare: Thinking About What Matters
