Orr stooped to unlace his shoes. He didn't want to get the Alien's bedspread dirty with his shoes; that would be scarcely a fair return for kindness. Stooping made him dizzy. "I am tired", he said. "I did a lot today. That is, I did something. The only thing I have ever done. I pressed a button. It took the entire willpower, the accumulated strengths of my entire existence, to press one damned OFF button."

